  "text": "[18F] FDG-PET has been used to assess alterations in glucose metabolism in the brain, cancer, cardiovascular diseases, and central nervous system disorders as well as in infectious, autoimmune, and inflammatory diseases [CITATION_1] , and has been evaluated in the diagnostic make-up for fever of unknown origin [CITATION_2] , where foci apparent on FDG-PET may not at all be visible on a contrast-enhanced CT. E. Bueding performed the first worm physiology experiments in 1950 and found schistosomes to be demanding consumers of glucose (Bueding 1950; [CITATION_3] ).",
